Pour the @water{240%ml} (see ingredients for amount) and the @Chicken Stock Powder{1} into a #saucepan{}, stir and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat and stirring in the @Couscous{120%g} and @Zhoug Style Paste{50%g}.

Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side for ~{8-10%mins} or until ready to serve.

While the couscous cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Trim the ends from the @Courgette{1}, halve lengthways, slice into 1cm wide strips, then chop into 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on a medium heat.

When hot, add the courgette and shallot. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Fry, stirring occasionally until softened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once the courgette has softened, add the @King Prawns{150%g} and @Chermoula Spice Mix{1}. Mix well and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Cook stirring occasionally until the prawns are cooked, ~{3-4%mins}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when they are pink on the outside and opaque inside.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}.

Add the prawns and veggies to the couscous and gently mix together.

Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Spoon the couscous and prawns into #bowls{}.

Spoon over the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!